clientbug is for reporting problems with the web client or connected
client-side interface, rather than a mudlib gameplay bug.

Syntax:

  clientbug <description>
  clientbug <object>:<description>

Examples:

  clientbug the achievements modal shows blank fields
  clientbug map: the minimap stops updating after I change floors

Clientbug reports are stored internally and mirrored to the GitHub issue
tracker with client-specific labels so they can be triaged separately
from game-world bugs.

Use the regular bug command for gameplay, room, mob, or command bugs
that are not specifically client-side.

See also: help bugs
